description: Book of Hours, Use of Sarum

metadata.label: Catalogue Description
metadata.value: Full catalogue record in Catalogue of Western Medieval Manuscripts in Oxford Libraries

metadata.label: Title
metadata.value: Book of Hours, Use of Sarum

metadata.label: Shelfmark
metadata.value: Bodleian Library MS. Lat. liturg. f. 21

metadata.label: Contents
metadata.value: Added 16th-cent. prayers (ff. 2v-3r). Prayer Auxiliatrix sis (f. 4). Office of the Virgin, with the Hours of the Cross worked in (ff. 5r-28v). Seven Joys of Our Lady (ff. 28v-29r). Variable parts of the office of the Virgin during the year (ff. 29v-41r). The Seven Penitential Psalms and the Fifteen Gradual Psalms (ff. 41v-48r). Litany (ff. 48r-52r). Office of the dead (ff. 52r-68r). Commendation (ff. 68v-77v). Variable parts of the litany for the days of the week except Monday (ff. 78r-83r). Psalms of the Passion (ff. 83v-91v). Added prayers (ff. 91v-92v).

metadata.label: Contents Note
metadata.value: Two strips from a 15th-century English gradual in the binding (ff. 1 and 96).

metadata.label: Layout
metadata.value: 21 long lines. Ruled in brown ink with 22 lines, the top, middle, and bottom pairs ruled the full width of the page; and single vertical bounding lines etending the full height of the page.

metadata.label: Extent
metadata.value: i (parchment strip) + ii (medieval paper) + 92 + ii (medieval paper) + i (modern paper) + i (parchment strip), foliated 1-96.

metadata.label: Decoration
metadata.value: Three historiated initials, all badly smudged, with foliate and pen-spray extensions forming partial borders: (fol. 5r) Hours of the Virgin: 9-line initial D[omine]: Annunciation. (fol. 41v) Penitential Psalms: 6-line initial D[omine]: Last Judgement. (fol. 68v) Commendation of Souls: 7-line initial B[eati]: Angels carrying a soul to heaven in a napkin. Five- or six-line initials in gold, on rose, blue, and white grounds, with foliate and pen-spray entensions to the first prayer and the hours from Lauds to Compline (fols. 4r, 9v, 19r, 21r, 22v, 24r, 25r, 26v). Two-line initials in blue with red penwork flourishing to psalms, prayers, etc.; one-line initials alternately plain red or blue to verses, etc.; line-fillers in the litanies alternately blue or red.

metadata.label: Binding
metadata.value: Sewn on three bands and half bound in 19th-cent. brown suede and gray paper over pasteboards.

metadata.label: Provenance
metadata.value: Possibly written for someone connected with the secular college of Wimbourne, Dorset, to judge by some of the prayers after Lauds in the Hours of the Virgin. 'Willelmus Weston de Lincolns Inn 1560' (fol. 2v). 'Ioannes Blykks (?)' (fol. 4). Sotheby's, October? 1903. Given by the executors of Dr. J. Wickham Legg, 1922.

metadata.label: Record Origin
metadata.value: Typescript description by Bodleian library staff, revised by Peter Kidd, late 1990s.
